verses.text_plain: The burden of Tyre. Howl, ye ships of Tarshish; for it is laid waste, so that there is no house, no entering in: from the land of Chittim it is revealed to them.
verses.verse_html: 1The burden of Tyre. Howl, ye ships of Tarshish; for it is laid waste, so that there is no house, no entering in: from the land of Chittim it is revealed to them.

tokens.text: so that there is no house

verses.text_plain: Be still, ye inhabitants of the isle; thou whom the merchants of Zidon, that pass over the sea, have replenished.
verses.verse_html:
2Be still, ye inhabitants of the isle; thou whom the merchants of Zidon, that pass over the sea, have replenished. ▼
▼ still: Heb. silent

verses.text_plain: And by great waters the seed of Sihor, the harvest of the river, is her revenue; and she is a mart of nations.
verses.verse_html: 3And by great waters the seed of Sihor, the harvest of the river, is her revenue; and she is a mart of nations.

verses.text_plain: Be thou ashamed, O Zidon: for the sea hath spoken, even the strength of the sea, saying, I travail not, nor bring forth children, neither do I nourish up young men, nor bring up virgins.
verses.verse_html: 4Be thou ashamed, O Zidon: for the sea hath spoken, even the strength of the sea, saying, I travail not, nor bring forth children, neither do I nourish up young men, nor bring up virgins.

verses.text_plain: As at the report concerning Egypt, so shall they be sorely pained at the report of Tyre.
verses.verse_html: 5As at the report concerning Egypt, so shall they be sorely pained at the report of Tyre.

verses.text_plain: Pass ye over to Tarshish; howl, ye inhabitants of the isle.
verses.verse_html: 6Pass ye over to Tarshish; howl, ye inhabitants of the isle.

verses.text_plain: Is this your joyous city, whose antiquity is of ancient days? her own feet shall carry her afar off to sojourn.
verses.verse_html:
7Is this your joyous city, whose antiquity is of ancient days? her own feet shall carry her afar off to sojourn. ▼
▼ afar…: Heb. from afar off

footnotes.body_html: ▼ afar…: Heb. from afar off

verses.text_plain: Who hath taken this counsel against Tyre, the crowning city, whose merchants are princes, whose traffickers are the honourable of the earth?
verses.verse_html: 8Who hath taken this counsel against Tyre, the crowning city, whose merchants are princes, whose traffickers are the honourable of the earth?

verses.text_plain: The Lord of hosts hath purposed it, to stain the pride of all glory, and to bring into contempt all the honourable of the earth.
verses.verse_html:
9The Lord of hosts hath purposed it, to stain the pride of all glory, and to bring into contempt all the honourable of the earth. ▼
▼ to stain: Heb. to pollute

footnotes.body_html: ▼ to stain: Heb. to pollute

verses.text_plain: Pass through thy land as a river, O daughter of Tarshish: there is no more strength.
verses.verse_html:
10Pass through thy land as a river, O daughter of Tarshish: there is no more strength. ▼
▼ strength: Heb. girdle

verses.text_plain: He stretched out his hand over the sea, he shook the kingdoms: the Lord hath given a commandment against the merchant city, to destroy the strong holds thereof.
verses.verse_html:
11He stretched out his hand over the sea, he shook the kingdoms: the Lord hath given a commandment against the merchant city, to destroy the strong holds thereof. ▼
▼ against…: or, concerning a merchantman
 , ▼
▼ the merchant city: Heb. Canaan
 , ▼
▼ strong…: or, strengths

footnotes.body_html: ▼ against…: or, concerning a merchantman
▼ the merchant city: Heb. Canaan

verses.text_plain: And he said, Thou shalt no more rejoice, O thou oppressed virgin, daughter of Zidon: arise, pass over to Chittim; there also shalt thou have no rest.
verses.verse_html: 12And he said, Thou shalt no more rejoice, O thou oppressed virgin, daughter of Zidon: arise, pass over to Chittim; there also shalt thou have no rest.

tokens.text: there also shalt thou have no rest

verses.text_plain: Behold the land of the Chaldeans; this people was not, till the Assyrian founded it for them that dwell in the wilderness: they set up the towers thereof, they raised up the palaces thereof; and he brought it to ruin.
verses.verse_html: 13Behold the land of the Chaldeans; this people was not, till the Assyrian founded it for them that dwell in the wilderness: they set up the towers thereof, they raised up the palaces thereof; and he brought it to ruin.

tokens.text: it for them that dwell in the wilderness

verses.text_plain: Howl, ye ships of Tarshish: for your strength is laid waste.
verses.verse_html: 14Howl, ye ships of Tarshish: for your strength is laid waste.

verses.text_plain: And it shall come to pass in that day, that Tyre shall be forgotten seventy years, according to the days of one king: after the end of seventy years shall Tyre sing as an harlot.
verses.verse_html:
15And it shall come to pass in that day, that Tyre shall be forgotten seventy years, according to the days of one king: after the end of seventy years shall Tyre sing as an harlot. ▼
▼ shall Tyre…: Heb. it shall be unto Tyre as the song of an harlot

tokens.text: And it shall come to pass in that day

footnotes.body_text: ▼ shall Tyre…: Heb. it shall be unto Tyre as the song of an harlot
footnotes.body_html: ▼ shall Tyre…: Heb. it shall be unto Tyre as the song of an harlot

verses.text_plain: Take an harp, go about the city, thou harlot that hast been forgotten; make sweet melody, sing many songs, that thou mayest be remembered.
verses.verse_html: 16Take an harp, go about the city, thou harlot that hast been forgotten; make sweet melody, sing many songs, that thou mayest be remembered.

verses.text_plain: And it shall come to pass after the end of seventy years, that the Lord will visit Tyre, and she shall turn to her hire, and shall commit fornication with all the kingdoms of the world upon the face of the earth.
verses.verse_html: 17And it shall come to pass after the end of seventy years, that the Lord will visit Tyre, and she shall turn to her hire, and shall commit fornication with all the kingdoms of the world upon the face of the earth.

tokens.text: And it shall come to pass after the end

verses.text_plain: And her merchandise and her hire shall be holiness to the Lord: it shall not be treasured nor laid up; for her merchandise shall be for them that dwell before the Lord, to eat sufficiently, and for durable clothing.
verses.verse_html:
18And her merchandise and her hire shall be holiness to the Lord: it shall not be treasured nor laid up; for her merchandise shall be for them that dwell before the Lord, to eat sufficiently, and for durable clothing. ▼
▼ durable: Heb. old

tokens.text: shall be for them that dwell
